HEADWORD: Boredom
<hw>Bore"dom</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
state of being bored, or pestered; a state of ennui.</def>
<rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The realm of bores; bores, collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boree</ent>⟦br⟧
